OSOGBO – Chief Gani Adams, the Aare OnaKakanfo has declared that he was ready to end insecurity in Yorubaland within the next four months. He stated this at a security retreat he held with members of Oodua Peoples Congress (OPC) in Osogbo. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Chief GaniAdams, who took advantage of the annual Osun Osogbo Festival to convey the meeting, said the group is ready to fight insecurity in the southwestern part of the country to standstill. He declared that he would use everything within his reach to end banditry, kidnapping and other sort of criminality in the southwest within the next four months. Adams said he was ordained as Aare Ona Kakanfo of Yoruba landandthatpartof hisdutiesis todefendandprotecttheYoruba people against any criminality. According tohim, “asthegeneralissimo of Yoruba land, my duty among others is to ensure thatYorubapeopleareprotected against any forces. “I am a warrior and I’m ordained to ensure that Yoruba people are protected. I am assuring you that I would use everything within my reach to make sure problem of insecurity becomes the issue of the past. I will make sure I crush the insecur